{"blocks":[{"key":"8l589","text":"A proportion of cells die when frozen, so it is better to transfer them all to the new flask, ensuring we got enough cells to seed the new culture.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ep18o","text":"Aspirate all medium in the flask.  Wash the cells with 5ml PBS.  Shake gently, then aspirate all the liquid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cleec","text":"Add 0.7ml of trypsin (for a T25) to the cells.  Incubate the flask at 37C for 5 minutes. {"blocks":[{"key":"dk03f","text":"While the cells are trypsinising, aspirate gelatine from the new flask and replace with 1-2ml of ES complete medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"drl4t","text":"Inactivate the trypsin by resuspending the cells in 4-5ml of ES complete medium. Make sure an even cell suspension is obtained by gently pipetting up and down.
